article.headline: Cornell 67, Yale 48
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Junior guard Alex Gamboa scored 16 points to lead Yale to 67-48 win over Cornell Saturday. Gamboa also played a key role in Yale's defense, holding Ka'Ron Barnes to 14 points on 4 of 16 shooting from the floor. Barnes leads the Ivy League in scoring with 21.8 points per game. Senior forward Matt Minoff had 14 points and eight rebounds and junior center Dominick Martin added 14 points and six rebounds for Yale (8-11, 3-3). The Bulldogs held Cornell to a season-low 48 points on 28.3 percent shooting. Cornell (10-9, 5-1) leads the Ivy League with 75.1 points per game. Junior center Eric Taylor had 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Big Red. Yale led by as many as 20 early in the second. Cornell pulled to within eight on several occasions, before Yale outscored the Big Red 14-3 over the final 7:23. Yale led 36-22 at the half.
